President Donald J. Trump will host and deliver a keynote speech at the Global Call to Protect Religious Freedom event on September 23, 2019, at the United Nations Headquarters. Vice President Mike Pence will also be present and will introduce President Trump. The event aims to garner international support to protect religious freedom in response to the increasing persecution of individuals based on their beliefs and the rising number of attacks on and destruction of places of worship. President Trump will urge the international community to take concrete measures to prevent attacks against people based on their religion or beliefs and to ensure the safety of houses of worship and public spaces for all faiths.